Class Project

  • java.lang.Object
    • lab10.Project
  • public class Project
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is implemented in accordance to the lab assignment but I have used some initiative for a few things. Project class works in harmony with Hackathon class and performs some utility actions to modify all scores, calculate the weighted average and store credibility of the Project instance.

      • Project

        public Project​(java.lang.String ID,
               int[] rawScores)
        The only constructor of Project. Initializes all required instance variables appropriately.
        Parameters:
        ID - The ID of the Project instance. It is expected to be in the format "X0" where X represents a String of length 1 and 0 represents a single digit number.
        rawScores - An int[] of length Hackathon.INDICATOR_COUNT that contains the raw scores of the Project instance that are going to be clamped to range (0, 100) according to a set of rules predetermined in the lab assignment.

      • calcModifiedScores

        public void calcModifiedScores()
        Uses the two-dimensional array INDICATOR_BOUNDARIES_AND_SCORES to easily modify each score of this The rawScores are clamped inside the range (0, 100) but only certain values are assigned. So this is not a scaling process Since the scores are now modified, status is now set to Project.MODIFIED

      • calcWeightAvg

        public void calcWeightAvg()
        This method calculates finalScore of this according to the indicator weights of hackathon The formula for this process is finalScore = (sum of each score * its weight) / (sum of all weigths) this needs to have hackathon initialized for this method to to work.
